<item>
            <title>[DERBY-1581] BasicDependencyManager re-loads the Provider multiple times from the DataDictionary when loading the stored dependencies for the Provider.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1581</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;From work on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1593&quot; title=&quot;Separate test jar files from the &amp;quot;product&amp;quot; jars in a distribution&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-1593&quot;&gt;DERBY-1593&lt;/a&gt; &amp;amp; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1330&quot; title=&quot;Provide runtime privilege checking for grant/revoke functionality&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-1330&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-1330&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;  it was discovered the DependencyMangerImpl  loaded the same Provier multiple times from the DataDictionary while loading the stored dependecies and converting them to an in-memory form.  There is no need to load the Provider from the  DataDictionary because it is passed into the DependencyManger.invalidateFor call that results in the loading of the stored dependencies.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
